Construct the split debug info compile unit for the debug info section.

In DWARF v5, the skeleton unit <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/die">DIE</a> may have the following attributes: DW&#95;AT&#95;addr&#95;base, DW&#95;AT&#95;comp&#95;dir, DW&#95;AT&#95;dwo&#95;name, DW&#95;AT&#95;high&#95;pc, DW&#95;AT&#95;low&#95;pc, DW&#95;AT&#95;ranges, DW&#95;AT&#95;stmt&#95;list, and DW&#95;AT&#95;str&#95;offsets&#95;base. Prior to DWARF v5 it may also have DW&#95;AT&#95;GNU&#95;dwo&#95;id. DW&#95;AT&#95;GNU&#95;dwo&#95;name is used instead of DW&#95;AT&#95;dwo&#95;name, Dw&#95;AT&#95;GNU&#95;addr&#95;base instead of DW&#95;AT&#95;addr&#95;base, and DW&#95;AT&#95;GNU&#95;ranges&#95;base instead of DW&#95;AT&#95;rnglists&#95;base.
